an identifier \[lq]foo\[rq],
followed by an invalid
character and then \[lq]bar\[rq],
is processed as \[lq]foobar\[rq].
.
.
.P
On a machine using the ISO 646,
8859,
or 10646 character encodings,
invalid input characters are
.BR 0x00 ,
.BR 0x08 ,
.BR 0x0B ,
.BR 0x0D \[en] 0x1F ,
and
.BR 0x80 \[en] 0x9F .
